We can’t control what happens to our luggage once it’s handed over at the airport. But we can control how we pack our bags. This can make all the difference if your bags are lost or delayed during your family vacation. 

Last year, our luggage was lost on two separate vacations, so I learned a lot about how to best pack. Sometimes, it’s not possible to only travel with carry on bags. There are definitely some things you can do to make sure that everyone in your family has at least have some essentials for a day or two. You’ll also want to make it easy for your bags to find their way back to you.

Here are our best tips - with more in our #linkinbio

You may be surprised at my answer to the question, Disneyland or Walt Disney World? As an East Coaster who grew up at Walt Disney World, it would be logical that I would prefer Walt Disney World. However, for families on their first Disney vacation, I actually would recommend Disneyland.

Disneyland is much more manageable, with two parks rather than four. The two are within easy walking distance, so park hopping is easy. The California weather is generally more pleasant than Central Florida’s weather. And, you’ll have a selection of both on and off property hotels in different price ranges. 

Which do you prefer? #disneyland #disneyblogger #igersdisney

Regardless of how long your NYC trip is, it’s impossible to see everything in the Big Apple in just one vacation. New York City is filled with museums, galleries, shops, landmarks, parks, theaters, and so much more. When planning your NYC trip, you are probably wondering how long to plan it for. I’ve found that 4 days in NYC is ideal – although you’ll definitely want to take more than one New York City trip to visit all of the main attractions.

Whether you are a first-time visitor to NYC or have visited multiple times, you’ll want to have a plan. Our sample four-day New York itinerary is a good starting point, especially for a first visit, but make modifications to personalize your experience. You may also want to switch around the days based on operating hours, weather, or other factors. ⁣

I haven’t been to the Magic Kingdom since the pandemic, so I knew I’d have to arrive at the Flock Conference a day early to enjoy some time. Luckily, it was well-timed with the recent opening of Tron 🏍️. I got up early, and after some technical difficulties, got my virtual boarding group. I also rode it’s a small world (always!), Thunder Mountain, Buzz Lightyear, and the Seven Dwarfs Mine Train. And of course, I watched the fireworks! 🎇

On Tuesday, I had the chance to ride the new Tron ride at the Magic Kingdom. This exciting new ride is unique and fun, but can be a challenge to actually experience.

To ride, you’ll need to either get an Individual Lightning Lane reservation (for a fee), or a spot in the virtual queue. You’ll need a park ticket and a park reservation to get either of these. 

Individual Lightning Lane reservations vary in price - for my visit, it was $20. You do not need Genie+, and you can choose your reservation window among the available times.

For the virtual queue, you need to get one exactly at 7am, or 1pm. There are also some released later in the evening for those eligible for extended hours. You don’t need to be in the park to get your boarding group, but you will need to try for one at the exact time the window opens. They are gone in seconds. 

Once you get a spot in the queue, you can enjoy the parks and keep an eye on how the queue is progressing. You’ll have an hour to return once your boarding group is called.

Because of the nature of the ride, you will need to store any belonging larger than a cell phone. Free lockers are available right before you board the ride. If you forget your locker number, you can scan your locker card or MagicBand to get the location. 

Have you been on Tron yet?.
#magickingdom #tronride #waltdisneyworld #familytravel

We received a complimentary room upgrade - The rooms at the Beaches Turks and Caicos Italian Village surround the Italian Village pool, which is the most popular, lively, and largest pool at the resort. In addition to the large pool, there is also a swim-up bar and a hot tub. This pool is where you’ll find many of the hosted activities, including water Zumba and trivia.

The Italian Village also borders the gorgeous beach. It’s an easy walk from any of the buildings down to the beach, and you’ll also be right near the water sports center for snorkeling and other water activities. #familytravel #beachesturksandcaicos #caribbeanvacation

The Courtyard Anaheim Theme Park Entrance Hotel, is located about a 5-10 minute walk from the front entrance of Disneyland in California. The hotel is great for families - it offers large guest rooms with two queen beds and bunk beds, as well as a separate shower, and a shower/tub combo.

When you want to take a break from the theme parks, you can spend some time in the small onsite water park, Surfside Waterpark, which is available exclusively to hotel guests. 

Check out our room tour and a view of the waterpark from our room. #disneyland #anaheimcalifornia #familytravel

During my recent trip to Disneyland, I found myself hungry at about 9:30am, after an extremely early breakfast (thanks to an early morning jet lagged wake up). I decided to put my name in at the Lamplight Lounge at Pixar Pier, a popular restaurant offering brunch on the weekends. While I wasn’t the only one with that idea, I was pleasantly surprised that I only had a 20 minute wait (although I’d definitely recommend getting a reservation if you can).

Brunch was fantastic. I started with their version of a Bloody Mary, and then got the Lamplight Chilaquiles, which were recommended by my server. Everything was delicious, and the location can’t be beat.
Thanks to @annievovan for these fantastic photos taken at Downtown Disney last week. Next time I’m in CA I’m definitely going to do some in the parks! @annievovanphotography

Despite waking up to some very heavy thunderstorms, the weather cleared and we had a great day at Isola Bella and Isola Del Pescatori in Lake Maggiore #abditalyswitzerland #lakemaggiore

We had a great day in Lake Como. We started with a bus ride from Lake Maggiore to Lake Como. After arriving, we took an Italian cooking class and then had a chef prepared lunch. Then we had a boat ride/tour with a stop at Villa Monastero. We finished with free time in town and then a great dinner. #lakecomo #lakecomoitaly
As we drive from Lake Maggiore to Zermatt for the 2nd part of our adventure, we made a quick stop at the Simplon Pass #abditalyswitzerland #familytravel

The most exciting part of our #abditalyswitzerland trip so far has been the ropes course and zip lines. Although I didn’t last too long, the rest of the family loved it. My 4’11” height proved to be a bit of a liability, but it was fun and beautiful! #zermattmatterhorn #zermatt
Before we left for Lucerne, I did one more walk through the quaint town of Zermatt, where no cars are allowed. #abditalyswitzerland #zermatt #zermattswitzerland #familytravel
This IceFlyer ride on Mt Titlis really feels like a real-life Soarin’ #abditalyswitzerland #mttitlis #switzerland

Lake Maggiore, Zermatt, and Lucerne are among the most beautiful places I’ve traveled to. Nine days was not enough time, but it was a good amount to get an appreciation for what each area has to offer. Like all of our ABD vacations, it was so nice to let someone else do the planning. #abditalyswitzerland #familytravel #zermatt #lakemaggiore 🇨🇭🇮🇹

The Rotair cable car at Mt. Titlis travels from the second gondola stop to the summit station at over 9,000 feet above sea level. During the 5 minute ride, the car rotates 360 degrees so you can get a complete view of the scenery.

This video is sped up, and in reality, the rotation is very slow. It’s a fun ride, and a great way to see the beautiful scenery. #abditalyswitzerland ⁣
#amazingswitzerland #switzerland #switzerland_vacations #swissalps #mountain #beautifulswitzerland #switzerlandtrip #inlovewithswitzerland #alps #switzerland🇨🇭 #visitswitzerland #traveltheworld

At Mt. Titlis in the Swiss Alps, you can walk through a glacier cave with ice is up to 5,000 years old. 🗻

While you are walking, don’t miss some of the fun photo opportunities, including a throne made of ice. Don’t forget your gloves and a sweatshirt or coat! 🥶
